Reset Your Privacy Settings In iOS 7

   by [29]Russell D. Vines on September 26, 2013

   If you recently upgraded, or are planning on upgrading, your iPhone or
   IPad to iOS 7, great! But there’s some privacy settings you should
   check out right after your upgrade. Some of these have been carried
   over from iOS 6, but the new integration features might not be right
   for you, especially if you’re not crazy about companies tracking
   everything you do on the phone.

   ZD Net has a good rundown on what you should check if you’re concerned
   about privacy. They suggest start by turning off:
     * Settings > Privacy > Location Services > System Services >
       Diagnostics & Usage
     * Settings > Privacy > Location Services > System Services >
       Location-Based iAds
     * Settings > Privacy > Location Services > System Services > Frequent
       Location

   It’s also a good idea to turn on “Limit Ad Tracking” in Settings >
   Privacy > Advertising, and also hit “Reset Advertising Identifier”.

   In your Safari settings, it’s another good idea to turn on Settings >
   Safari > Do Not Track

   [30]http://www.zdnet.com/four-privacy-settings-you-should-enable-in-ios
   -7-immediately-7000020902/

   This site also has some good privacy pointers:

   [31]http://ios.wonderhowto.com/how-to/18-sneaky-privacy-betraying-setti
   ngs-every-iphone-owner-must-know-about-ios-7-0148682/

   Happy upgrading!

